phase_3_consolidation_schema.instruction:
CREATE consolidation decision matrix with explicit determinations:

For each artifact, determine and store:
  ARTIFACT: {Current Name}
  STATUS: {RETAIN as Canon | RETAIN as Periphery | DELETE}
  NEW NAME: {Proposed canonical name, or "—" if deleting}
  ROLE: {One-line description of function/purpose}
  RATIONALE: {Why retain or why delete}

DECISION PRINCIPLE:
  - CANON: Self-standing, foundational, irreplaceable intellectual content
  - RETAINED PERIPHERY: Operationalizes or enables Canon; essential supporting structure
  - DELETE: Scaffolding, intermediate work, noise, superseded, duplicative — dissolved completely

This matrix drives the two output artifacts (see Phase 4)
